M|Matc|tx|\| pd Characteristic \| Best Engine \| Why \|
M|Matc|tx|\|----------------------\|-------------\|-----\|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd involves collaboration btw us \| Viral \| Natural sharing built into usage \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd has hi switching costs and repeat use \| Sticky \| Retention is the natural advantage \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd has clear, quantifiable ROI \| Paid \| Easy to justify acquisition spend \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd is novel and share-worthy \| Viral \| Word of mouth drives awareness \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd has hi LTV and long sales cycle \| Paid \| Justify hi CAC w/ hi LTV \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd creates data/cn that compounds \| Sticky \| Accumulated value prevents churn \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd output is visible to non-us \| Viral \| Built-in exposure mechanism \|
M|Matc|tx|\| pd is in a crowded mk w/ lo differentiation \| Paid \| Outspend cr efficiently \|
M|Deci|it|[ ] What is the natural behavior of your cs after using the pd? (Share it, keep using it, or recommend it when asked?)
M|Deci|it|[ ] Does your pd inherently involve other people?
M|Deci|it|[ ] What is your cs's lifetime value potential?
M|Deci|it|[ ] Can you measure and attribute acquisition sources?
M|Deci|it|[ ] What is the competitive landscape? (Viral markets tend toward winner-take-all)
